<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - ASSEMBLE - SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Pins on the LO range synchronizer must line up with the chamfered holes on the sliding clutch bottom.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the larger LO range synchronizer ring face down (with pins up) on a bench (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017g1">Figure 161</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017g1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017g1" filename="../figg13/G13017g1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 161. Synchronizer Assembly Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the sliding clutch recessed side up, place the sliding clutch on the LO range
                synchronizer pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017g1">Figure 161</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">In the HI range synchronizer bores, install the three (3) springs (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017g2">Figure 162</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017g2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017g2" filename="../figg13/G13017g2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 162. Three Springs - HI Range Synchronizer Bores</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the HI range synchronizer ring over the LO range synchronizer ring. Rotate the HI
                range synchronizer until the springs are seated against the pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017g3">Figure 163</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017g3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017g3" filename="../figg13/G13017g3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 163. Springs Seated Against Pins</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply downward pressure to the HI range synchronizer ring while twisting counterclockwise (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017g4">Figure 164</hotlnk>). This compresses the springs to fully seat HI range on
                the LO range synchronizer.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017g4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017g4" filename="../figg13/G13017g4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 164. Pressure To HI Range Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
